      "summary": "Ammit (also spelled Ammut, Ahemait, or Am-mut) is one of ancient Egypt's most fearsome supernatural entities - a hybrid demon creature that devoured the hearts of the wicked in the afterlife judgment hall.",
      "full": "Ammit (also spelled Ammut, Ahemait, or Am-mut) is one of ancient Egypt's most fearsome supernatural entities - a hybrid demon creature that devoured the hearts of the wicked in the afterlife judgment hall. Part crocodile, part lion, and part hippopotamus, Ammit represented the ultimate spiritual death: the complete annihilation of the soul. Unlike gods who could be appeased or demons who could be bargained with, Ammit was an implacable force of divine justice that consumed those who failed the weighing of the heart ceremony."
